On April 13, they showed up to the crossing at 4:30 a.m., joining dozens of other asylum seekers with court dates originally scheduled for that morning.
Even though the groups are able to secure the reschedule notices for asylum seekers from a distance, that has created a new problem.
Some of the most dangerous areas for violence and extortion targeting asylum seekers is the Texas border with the Mexican state of Tamaulipas.
In Nogales, her team offers consultations and workshops for asylum seekers to help fill out their paperwork.
Normally, her team can count on as many as 25 volunteers to help provide access to counsel to asylum seekers at the border.